column8:
The revised approach for the L Project means that we'll be able to run service on the L at all times, with reduced service on nights and weekends. We've created an alternate service plan to help you navigate starting April 26, 2019 through summer 2020. Use this page to learn more about travel tips and construction progress.

Major service changes on the L train began last night and will last through Summer 2020. L trains will run every 20 minutes between Brooklyn and Manhattan during evenings, nights, and weekends. Plan ahead for a faster trip. We are increasing service on other train lines and adding bus service to help you avoid less frequent and crowded trains. To learn more about all of your service options, visit mta.info and click on "L Project" or stop by a Station agent.

M train riders - We're increasing and expanding M train service to help provide additional service during the L Project's service changes. On weeknights, M trains will run more frequently on their regular route between Metropolitan Av and Forest Hills-71 Av. Starting at 10 pm, trains will go to 96 St-2 Av in Manhattan instead of Forest Hills-71 Av. On weekends, M trains will be also extended to 96 St-2 Av at all times and run more frequently (every 8 minutes). Learn more about the L Project and all of your travel options here: https://new.mta.info/l-project
